Ciudad de Buenos Aires&#8221;, 2008, both available on the Ombudsman&#8217;s Office website at 
www.defensoria.org.ar/areastematicas/vivienda10.php. According to the Ombudsman&#8217;s Office of the 
Autonomous City of Buenos Aires, for example, the number of people living in slums rose by 300 per 
cent between 1983 and 1991 and by a further 150 per cent in the last decade, to stand at more than 
120,000 people in 2006. Furthermore, there are 200,000 people living in squats and a further 70,000 
in makeshift dwellings. See also Zayat and Ricciardi, &#8220;El derecho a la defensa ...&#8221; (footnote 7 above). 
</p>
